sql:
SELECT DISTINCT b.listing_id
FROM bookings b
JOIN listings l ON b.listing_id = l.listing_id;

external_knowledge:
- "voyagers" refers to the tenants who have made bookings;
- "ships" metaphorically refers to the properties or listings;
- "fare" is a metaphor for the monthly rent of the properties;
- "vessels currently ready to set sail" refers to properties with an availability status of 'Available'.

- 'Calcutta’ is the older name for ‘Kolkata’.;
- The preferred number of bedrooms ('preferred_bhk') of the tenants matches the actual number of bedrooms ('bhk') in the properties, symbolizing a perfect fit; 
- The 'bookings' and 'views' are indicators of the popularity and desirability of the properties.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT properties.property_id, properties.description
